    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>4 hard-boiled eggs, peeled and halved</li>
            <li>1 cup chickpea flour (besan)</li>
            <li>1/4 cup rice flour</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon red chili powder</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon cumin powder</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon coriander powder</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon baking soda</li>
            <li>Salt, to taste</li>
            <li>Water, as needed</li>
            <li>Vegetable oil, for frying</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a bowl, combine chickpea flour, rice flour, red chili powder, turmeric powder, cumin powder, coriander powder, baking soda, and salt.</li>
            <li>Add water gradually to the dry ingredients, whisking continuously, until you get a smooth batter with a thick consistency. Ensure there are no lumps.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a deep pan for frying over medium heat.</li>
            <li>Dip each hard-boiled egg half into the batter, ensuring it is well-coated.</li>
            <li>Gently place the coated egg into the hot oil and fry until golden brown and crispy. Repeat for all egg halves.</li>
            <li>Remove the egg pakodas from the oil and place them on paper towels to absorb excess oil.</li>
            <li>Serve the Egg Pakodas hot with your favorite chutney or sauce.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your crunchy and flavorful Egg Pakodas!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

